name: SHAIKHA LATIFAH AHMED JUMA
bio: [('Beginning', 'Her parents and uncles taught her to ride as a child, and she began competing in jumping at age 13. "My family is all about horses, but more in endurance and racing. I am the only one who got into show jumping." (sport360.com, 22 Nov 2012; horsetimesegypt.com, 2008)'), ('Reason', '"The horses are what I love most about this sport. I love the process of getting a horse and building them up from nothing. I really love that. I have always done it. With Kalaska, I had him since he was seven and we went all the way up together. I love being in the big classes and in the big sport, but more than that the process of taking horses as far as they can go. That is my passion." (worldofshowjumping.com, 07 Feb 2018)'), ('Coach', 'Ramzy Al Duhami, UAE (livingpolo.com, 17 Feb 2018; worldofshowjumping.com, 07 Feb 2018)'), ('Training', 'She incorporates gym and CrossFit training into her daily regime. "Working out keeps me sane, I\'ve always liked training, but CrossFit I am addicted to." (worldofshowjumping.com, 07 Feb 2018; cyrinecherif.com, 2017)'), ('Ambition', 'To compete at the 2020 Olympic Games in Tokyo. (worldofshowjumping.com, 07 Feb 2018)'), ('Additional Information', 'GeneralRESIDENCEShe splits her time between the United Arab Emirates and Europe, where she trains with Ramzy Al Duhami. "I am based in Europe for six months every year, in Normandy [France] and with Ramzy. I have also worked a little bit with Ludger Beerbaum and Philipp Weishaupt." (worldofshowjumping.com, 07 Feb 2018)CROSSFIT BUILDS CONFIDENCEShe took up CrossFit after an injury in 2016, and it has since become an integral part of her training. "I train a lot. I am so small, and my horses are big. When I don\'t train I am in agony. I think that for your mental strength, fitness is really important. I train Cross Fit. I started doing it after I had an accident in 2016. I lost a bit of my confidence and I needed something to push me. With the heavier weights, and doing things that you are not comfortable with and that you are bad at - that makes you better. I believe in working on your weaknesses." (worldofshowjumping.com, 07 Feb 2018) '), ('Hero', 'German jumper Marcus Ehning. (sport360.com, 22 Nov 2012)'), ('Relatives', 'She is a member of the royal family in the United Arab Emirates. Her cousin Sheikh Juma Al Maktoum competed in shooting at the 2012 Olympic Games in London. Another cousin, Maitha Al Maktoum, competed in taekwondo at the 2008 Olympic Games in Beijing. (horsetimesegypt.com, 2008; sports-reference.com, 2016)'), ('Languages', 'Arabic, English'), ('Highlights', 'RankEventYearLocationAsian Games2Jumping Individual2010Guangzhou, CHN2Jumping Team2010Guangzhou, CHN3Jumping Team2006Doha, QAT4Jumping Individual2014Incheon, KOR4Jumping Team2014Incheon, KOR20Jumping Individual2006Doha, QATOlympic Games48Jumping Individual2008Beijing, CHNWorld Equestrian Games24Jumping Team2010Lexington, KY, USA88Jumping Individual2010Lexington, KY, USAWorld Cup Arab League1Jumping Individual2014/2015Sharjah, UAE11Jumping Individual2017/2018Sharjah, UAE11Jumping Individual2016/2017Al Ain, UAE21Jumping Individual2017/2018Dubai, UAEWDWJumping Individual2016/2017Dubai, UAE')]

name: Victor
bio: [('Additional Information', 'Preferred techniquesYoko-wakare (IJF, 17 Jul 2016)GeneralMOVE TO UAEIn 2013 he switched his allegiance from the Republic of Moldova to the United Arab Emirates. (gulfnews.com, 17 Sep 2014)NATIONAL FIRSTHe was the first athlete representing the United Arab Emirates in judo to win a medal at the world championships, claiming bronze in the 73kg category at the 2014 edition in Chelyabinsk, Russian Federation. (SportsDeskOnline, 26 Jul 2018; sport360.com, 04 Aug 2016)EARLY SETBACKAlong with fellow former Republic of Moldova-born judoka Mihail Marchitan and Ivan Remarenco, he was selected for the UAE team to compete at the 2014 Asian Games in Incheon, Republic of Korea. name: Sergiu
bio: [('Awards', 'He was named the 2011 Moldovan Athlete of the Year. (publika.md, 16 Dec 2011)'), ('Additional Information', "Preferred techniquesYoko-wakare (IJF, 17 Jul 2016)GeneralCOMPETING FOR UNITED ARAB EMIRATESHe represented the Republic of Moldova at the 2012 Olympic Games in London before switching nationality and starting to compete for the United Arab Emirates. He was one of six judoka, along with national coach Vasile Colta, to leave the Republic of Moldova and take up citizenship in the United Arab Emirates in 2013. (publika.md, 04 Nov 2013; protv.md, 15 Jul 2013)HISTORIC ACHIEVEMENTHe became the first athlete representing the United Arab Emirates to claim a medal in judo at the Olympic Games when he took bronze in the 81kg category at the 2016 Games in Rio de Janeiro. The medal was only the second won by an Emirati athlete at the Olympic Games, following Ahmed Almaktoum's gold in shooting [double trap] at the 2004 Games in Athens. (SportsDeskOnline, 09 Aug 2016) "), ('Injuries', 'He was out for a year due to injury, returning to the sport at the 2014 IPIC Abu Dhabi Judo Grand Slam in the United Arab Emirates.
